AMIGA Time & Magik has:
 picture cache to reduce unnecessary disc loads;
 edit previous commands, by cursor keys and BACKSPACE;
 SAVE/RESTORE to disc;
 RAM SAVE/RESTORE in memory;
 UNDO (take back moves);

(When saving, if a drive name is not given, the file will by default be
written to drive df0: If you have two drives you may wish to use a fuller
filename eg. df1:saves/save9 ).

HARD DISCS. Time and Magik is supplied on floppy disc, but we are pretty
confident that it should work on other disc drives too. (No promises! This
is a free extra feature, so it's not a bug if the game won't work on your
peculiar disc drive.) Just copy the disc, file by file, into a folder of
your choice, and run it by clicking on MENU.

Compatibility: the adventure interpreter on this disc also works with
Knight Orc and Gnome Ranger. Copy your original and replace MENU, GAME1 
and PICPROC by the new ones.

Please remember that Level 9 games are protected by copyright and take a
long time to produce, so only make one copy, for your own use, to keep
only as long as you have the original game.

Happy Adventuring!

